definitions.definition: Of a cell, having a pair of each type of chromosome , one of the pair being derived from the ovum and the other from the spermatozoon . Most somatic cells of higher organisms are diploid.
Of an organism, having diploid cells.
Of a certain symmetry class with 24 congruent irregular quadrilateral faces .
